<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-390-494  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 390 494.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  June 26 1989 n321 p76(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MicroAge to adopt cost-plus pricing. (MicroAge Computer StoresInc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kinley, Patricia.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MicroAge Computer Stores will drop its 5.9 percent royalties toits franchise stores in favor of cost-plus pricing.andP;  Each productline offered franchises will have a different percentage of markupunder the new plan.andP;  Store owners will also pay shipping chargesfor products ordered.andP;  The plan has reportedly been put intoeffect with some dealers in the chain, but not all have beenofficially notified of the change.andP;  Critics suggest the new policymay help high-volume outlets because the chain's markup will bedetermined by purchases at each store.andP;  Of all franchise computerchains, only ValCom Inc and Computerland now maintain a royaltyprice structure.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MicroAge Computer Stores Inc. (distribution).andO;Topic:     CostPricing PolicyNew TechniqueComputer RetailingChain StoresFranchisePrice.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>